  <p class="field-ns-blog-post-lead">
    We have a new file called .editorconfig in the root folder of Drupal 8. Behind this file there is a very interesting initiative that is worth spreading.  </p>
<div class="field-ns-blog-post-body clearfix">
            <div class="field-item even"> <p> </p><p><img alt="editorconfig_header.png" class="media-image" height="100" title="editorconfig_header.png" width="737" src="http://wunderkraut.com/sites/wunderkraut.com/files/field_ns_prod_entrpr_thumbnail/editorconfig_header.png" /></p><p>The project <a href="http://editorconfig.org">EditorConfig</a> tries to promote the idea of having a <strong>.editorconfig</strong> file in each of your projects, so you can enjoy a consistent coding style between different editors and IDEs. No need to configure anymore the editor for every project.</p><p>The text format of <em>.editorconfig</em> is easy to read. For example this is the current <em>.editorconfig</em> in Drupal8 alpha 4:</p>
<pre>

# Drupal editor configuration normalization
# @see http://editorconfig.org/

# This is the top-most .editorconfig file; do not search in parent directories.
root = true

# All files.
[*]
end_of_line = LF
indent_style = space
indent_size = 2

# Not in the spec yet:
# @see https://github.com/editorconfig/editorconfig/wiki/EditorConfig-Properties
charset = utf-8
trim_trailing_whitespace = true
insert_final_newline = true
</pre>
<p> </p><p>In this file is expressed in a concise and readable manner some basic conventions part of the <a href="https://drupal.org/coding-standards">Drupal coding standards</a>.</p><p>To make use of the the <em>.editorconfig</em> file, you need to install the plugin in your favourite editor to make it happen:</p><p><img alt="editorconfig_plugins.png" class="media-image" height="418" title="editorconfig_plugins.png" width="480" src="http://wunderkraut.com/sites/wunderkraut.com/files/styles/large/public/editorconfig_plugins.png?itok=m0uQiF3y" /><br />The success of the project EditorConfig relies on how far the initative spreads, and how many text editors and IDEs support this brilliant initiative.</p><p>Not only Drupal, but many other open source projects have included this editorconfig file as part of their repositories: jQuery, Ruby, Symfony, CakePHP, Octopress, Modernizr, etc and <a href="https://github.com/editorconfig/editorconfig/wiki/Projects-Using-EditorConfig">many others</a>.</p><p>When the <em>.editorconfig</em> file was <a href="https://drupal.org/node/1713662">committed to Drupal 8</a> in Dec 2012 there were some doubts about its usefulness and the issue was marked with the "<em>review before release</em>" tag. But I believe this file will stay with us for a long time.<br /> </p><p> </p> </div>
